Package uk.ac.ed.inf.DronePath

Class Drone

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.ed.inf.DronePath.Drone
public class Drone extends Object
Drone class is the body of the system and brings together all the functionalities. It is a virtual representation of a drone that also simulates its limitations. It generates an optimal path and traverses through Edinburgh city to deliver pizza orders.

  • Method Details

    • deliverOrders

      public List<Output> deliverOrders(String orderDate)
      Function validates each order and processes its outcome. Order details, time taken to calculate the path, and the order's delivery path are stored to a list of Output.
      Parameters:
      orderDate - String date to get a specific day's list of Order.
      Returns:
      Returns a list of Output consisting of the outcomes of a processed Order.

    • getTotalFlightPath

      public List<PathNode> getTotalFlightPath()
      Getter function for total flight paths travelled
      Returns:
      Returns a list of PathNode consisting of all paths taken when delivering Order.

    • getSortedOrders

      public PriorityQueue<Order> getSortedOrders(Restaurant[] restaurants, Order[] orders, HashMap<Restaurant,List<PathNode>> restaurantPath)
      Helper function for sorting a list of orders
      Parameters:
      restaurants - List of Restaurant from the ILP REST server.
      orders - List of Order from the ILP REST server.
      restaurantPath - HashMap of Restaurant paired with the list of PathNode from Appleton Tower to the restaurant.
      Returns:
      Returns a priority queue which sorts Order according to the number of moves required for the Drone to deliver the orders.

    • generateOutput

      public Output generateOutput(Order order, List<PathNode> path)
      Helper function that generates the output for an order and adds to total flight path
      Parameters:
      order - Order to be processed.
      path - List of PathNode from Appleton Tower to the order's Restaurant.
      Returns:
      Output with the outcome of the Order processed.
